author: NihilistHUGZ
body: Over the past few months I have learned a vast amount of the structure for bots or algorithmic trading. They are set to identify buy and sell signals based on metrics which track several different values lile rules. A human requires years of experience to recognize these same patterns but even then there is no competition for the algorithm that identifies those same patterns to the 'value' meaning higher frequency of potential trades.  One of the greatest challenges is the frequency of these trades and keeping up with them. They also work against each other as well as many people use them. So if someone improperly sets the rules for the algorithm the consequences affects the other bots and humans in a terrible cycle.  These algorithms are set by large investors and other companies pay for these service to do everything from provide liquidity/suck liquidity, false flag dumps, market aggregates, and many other ways to benefit and harm the process movements of EVERY ASSET CLASS NOT JUST CRYPTO.  The bots dont stop at the charts they are in every forum on every platform and in every way influencing the psychology of the average investor as well.

author: NihilistHUGZ
body: I can't even tell you how bad it really is. Watch out for holdiays where they leave their bots running and go on vacation.
